-- Suzlon Energy Wins Order for 49 Wind Turbines From India’s ONGC
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2013-02-26T06:07:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-26/suzlon-energy-wins-order-for-49-wind-turbines-from-india-s-ongc.html
Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)  won an order to
install 49 wind turbines from  Oil & Natural Gas Corp. (ONGC) ,  India ’s
biggest energy explorer.  ONGC will buy Suzlon’s S88 2.1-megawatt turbines to be set
up in the north western state of Rajasthan, Suzlon, India’s
largest wind-turbine maker, said in an e-mailed statement today.  Suzlon, based in Pune, will complete the project in the
financial year ending March 31, 2014. It had earlier set up 51
megawatts in Gujarat for ONGC, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
